Claims CLAIMS WHAT IS CLAIMED: 1. A system for scanning documents, the system comprising: an input tray for holding one or more documents to be scanned; a transport drive system configured to move a document of the one or more documents along a document transport path; at least one gate element configured to: engage with lead edges of the documents held by the input tray; oscillate forward and backward in respect to the document transport path according to one or more oscillation parameters to align the lead edges of the documents; and disengage with the lead edges of the documents held by the input tray to allow the documents to be transported along the document transport path. 2. The system of claim 1, wherein the at least one gate element is coupled to a drive shaft of the transport drive system and the drive shaft rotates according to the one or more oscillation parameters to oscillate the at least one gate element forward and backward along the document transport path. 3. The system of claim 2, wherein the one or more oscillation parameters include at least one of an amplitude, a frequency of oscillation, a total number of oscillation cycles, an acceleration of the feeder gate elements, a deceleration of the feeder gate elements, and how long to pause between each oscillation. 4. The system of claim 3, wherein the one or more oscillation parameters are based on a type of material of the documents inserted into the input tray, a number of documents inserted into the input tray, a width of the documents, and a length of the documents. 5. The system of claim 1, wherein disengaging with the lead edges of the documents includes retracting the at least one gate element into a frame body of the system. 6. The system of claim 2, wherein the at least one gate element includes a down position stop, the down position stop configured to engage with a frame stop to constrain a forward movement of the feeder gate element in respect to the document transport path. 7. The system of claim 6, wherein the down position stop includes a magnetized element and wherein the frame stop includes a ferromagnetic material such that the down position stop and the frame stop are attracted to one another. 8. The system of claim 2, wherein the at least one gate element includes an up position stop, the up position stop configured to engage with a frame stop to constrain a backward movement of the feeder gate element in respect to the document transport path. 9. The system of claim 1, wherein the oscillation forward and backward in respect to the document transport path causes the documents engaged with the at least one feeder gate element to slide between each other and to move towards the at least one feeder gate element, aligning the lead edges of the documents. 10. The system of claim 1, further comprising: a feeder roller configured to transport a document from the input tray into the document transport path within the scanner; detection sensors configured to detect leading and trailing edges of the document transported along the document transport path; and at least one imaging device configured to image the document and provide digital image data to a processor. 11. A method of aligning documents for a scanning device, the method comprising: determining documents are present in an input tray of the scanning device, the leading edges of the documents being engaged with at least one feeder gate element of the scanning device in a blocking position; 

 oscillating the at least one feeder gate element forward and backward in respect to a document transport path of the scanning device according to one or more oscillation parameters to align the lead edges of the documents; retracting the at least one feeder gate element to a retracted position to clear the document transport path; separating a document from the documents in the input tray of the scanning device; and transporting the separated document along the document transport path within the scanning device. 12. The method of claim 11, further comprising: determining each document of the documents has been scanned; and raising the at least one feeder gate element to the blocking position to block the document transport path. 13. The method of claim 11, wherein oscillating the at least one feeder gate element forward and backward in respect to the document transport path causes the documents engaged with the at least one feeder gate element to slide between each other and to move towards the at least one feeder gate element, aligning the lead edges of the documents. 14. The method of claim 11, wherein the at least one gate element is coupled to a drive shaft of a transport drive system and wherein the drive shaft rotates according to the one or more oscillation parameters to oscillate the at least one gate element forward and backward in respect to the document transport path. 15. The method of claim 11, wherein the one or more oscillation parameters include at least one of an amplitude, a frequency of oscillation, a total number of oscillation cycles, an acceleration of the feeder gate elements, a deceleration of the feeder gate elements, and how long to pause between each oscillation. 16. The method of claim 11, wherein the one or more oscillation parameters are based on a type of material of the documents inserted into the input tray, a number 

 of documents inserted into the input tray, a width of the documents, and a length of the documents. 17. The method of claim 14, wherein the at least one gate element includes a down position stop, the down position stop configured to engage with a frame stop to constrain a forward movement of the feeder gate element in respect to the document transport path. 18. The method of claim 17, wherein the down position stop includes a magnetized element and wherein the frame stop includes a ferromagnetic material such that the down position stop and the frame stop are attracted to one another. 19. The method of claim 14, wherein the at least one gate element includes an up position stop, the up position stop configured to engage with a frame stop to constrain a backward movement of the feeder gate element in respect to the document transport path. 20. The method of claim 11, further comprising: transporting the document sheet along the document transport path using one or more drive motors and transport rollers; detecting the lead and trailing edges of the document sheet transported along the document transport path; and imaging the sheet with an imaging device along the transport path and provide digital image data to a processor.
